	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ah k. My Turn. Again, I'll repeat what others have said. One class doesn't own another, it's random due to resists, luck, and skill. Also, fear CAN be casted on PCs again. It has a high high resist rate on them is all so you might as well forget about casting it on them. I, as a necro, have always wanted to know how to crush a wizard in a duel, and even lost one to Nizz who posted much earlier. (damn you nizz lol) He didn't manage to root my pet but went for me instead. I was lvl 38 and he was lvl 42 if I remember correctly. Well, my lvl 34 pet was a flat out puss. Miss, Miss, Hit for 34. Heh. Wasn't pretty. I was so concerned about my life, every time he nuked me I'd do my lvl 29 life spike (next one is at 39 which was one lvl away). This healed about 1 bubble of my life or so. Well I got down to about 2 bubbles of health and kept trying to get health back but he smacked me down with that last nuke. I've done some thinking on possible ways to beat a wiz. If you can hit them with fear, they are completely dead. I still need to do some testing with that on PCs. What you need to do is (this is not considering the RoK spells for either class. I assume it will be much harder with their damn torrent of fire shat.) cast your fastest dot with considerable damage at the very first. Watch them, and if they start to cast IC, use harmshield. ONLY use harmshield when its IC. This being because you wont be able to cast it again until u die, zone, or let it pop back up. So, actually wait to see what they cast first. Start casting boil blood first thing. If they cast IC this first time, it should be no problem.. It will take u to low health but you've already won. Boil blood has them owned (whether you die or not.. if they dont dispell that is) Just harmshield and let the pet whack them. Now harmshield will only last 18 seconds... Hardly the 2 minutes u need from boil blood. Assuming they dont root your pet they should be at about 1/2 health. As soon as harmshield falls use lvl 49 tap. this will take them to about 1 bubble. Now use either ignite bones or shock of poison depending on your life and theirs. If you have decent life after the tap then use ignite bones (500 dd) unless they have extremely low health. If they have extremly low health use shock of poison (160 dd with 3 second cast time). Shock of poison being a much faster cast will finish them off if they have low health. On the other hand if they have more health u should stick to ignite bones (6 seconds i believe) which would be more valuable than 2 shock of poisons in that time considering the crystals have to pop up yatta yatta. So basically thats the way you win. Now i dont know if its true that wiz's have 1000hp at lvl 50 but if so, ignite bones alone would take half. That's the way you should destroy a wiz =)<BR>
<BR>
~Rystos D`Vantigom<BR>
L47 Prexus Necro<BR>
PS: I'll get you Nizz. You'll see.
				</font>
