	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hullo all, This may clear a little up.<BR>
<BR>
 If you think about it, the chances for a nec over wiz are equal to the wiz over nec. I've seen three battles, both level 50s. <BR>
Nec w/ NO EXP or tatics VS. Wiz w/ EXP and tactics. Wizard won, Necro just casted like crazy not thinking of stacking DOTs or anything.<BR>
Nec w/ EXP and tactics VS. Wiz w/ NO EXP or tactics. Nec won, The wizard was casting supernova etc, and pounding the nec's pet. After the pet died, Wiz was OOM and the nec, sadly, just completey burned that poor lil' wizard.<BR>
Nec w/ EXP and tactics VS. Wiz w/ EXP and tactics.<BR>
This was a close one, the nec won. The nec was on a losing streak, The wizard over-whelmed the nec, and that made him forget about the pet. The wiz ICed the nec a couple, then did some interrupting spells, after that, he had I belive 1 bub of mana left, the nec, a half bub left. NOW, if the fight was wiz to wiz, the wiz with a 1bub of mana would win. INSTEAD, the nec got lucky, sent over a few DoTs stacking them, got his pet into auction. The wizard, casting some awesome spells, ALMOST killed the nec. They both got knocked out, loosing blood, I thought it was a tie, but the DoTs kicked in more and finished the wizard off, and then the nec died, so the nec won.<BR>
<BR>
My conclusion is that the wizard thought he had the nec owned, but (stupidty to our class wizards) he forgot about the DoTs, and, the pet. So, just to all you out their, the fights are even, you must have EXP and tactics to own another, and the duels are circles, everyone can kill everyone. If I was the wizard, I would have use my most upgraded root spell (forgot what is was called) and root the pet, then IC the necro and try to finish him off before the DoTs got in, knowing I would die anyway because of the DoTs, Well, there's my post, I hope it clears things up.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
